recalls.Summary: Subaru of America, Inc. (Subaru) is recalling certain 2012-2014 Subaru Impreza, 2012-2013 Impreza Stationwagon, 2013 Subaru BRZ, XV Crosstrek and Toyota Scion FR-S vehicles.  The engine valve springs in these vehicles may fracture causing an engine malfunction or a possible engine stall.
recalls.Consequence: An engine stall can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Subaru will notify their owners.  Toyota will notify the FR-S owners.  Dealers will replace the valve springs, free of charge.  The recall began December 26, 2018.  Subaru owners may contact Subaru customer service at 1-844-373-6614, Toyota owners may contact the Toyota Customer Experience Center at 1-888-270-9371.  Subaru's number for this recall is WTY-84.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: SUBARU IS RECALLING CERTAIN MODEL YEAR 2013 BRZ VEHICLES MANUFACTURED FROM NOVEMBER 25, 2011, THROUGH MAY 25, 2012.  THE OWNERS MANUAL CONTAINS AN INACCURATE DESCRIPTION OF THE ACTUAL OPERATION OF THE FRONT PASSENGER OCCUPANT CLASSIFICATION SYSTEM.  OTHER PORTIONS OF THE OWNERS MANUAL, DESCRIBING THE AIR BAG SYSTEM, REQUIRE CLARIFICATION.  AS SUCH, THESE VEHICLES FAIL TO COMPLY WITH FEDERAL MOTOR VEHICLE SAFETY STANDARD (FMVSS) NO. 208, OCCUPANT CRASH PROTECTION.
recalls.Consequence: MISINFORMATION COULD LEAD TO AN INCREASED RISK OF INJURY TO FRONT SEAT OCCUPANTS DURING CERTAIN CRASH CONDITIONS.
recalls.Remedy: SUBARU WILL NOTIFY OWNERS, AND WILL MAIL CORRECTED OWNERS MANUALS, FREE OF CHARGE.  THE SAFETY RECALL BEGAN ON JUNE 19, 2012.  OWNERS MAY CONTACT SUBARU AT 1-800-782-2783.
recalls.Notes: SUBARU'S RECALL CAMPAIGN NUMBER IS WQB-38.  CUSTOMERS MAY CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S VEHICLE SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-327-4236 (TTY: 1-800-424-9153); OR GO TO HTTP://WWW.SAFERCAR.GOV.

complaints.summary: The contact owns a 2013 Subaru BRZ. The contact stated while driving approximately 30 MPH, the vehicle stalled. The contact stated that several unknown warning lights illuminated. From the very first day I had these brakes pads installed they performed terribly. At low speeds, under 25mph, they would shriek and slightly shake the vehicle; far worse response at higher speeds. I read somewhere online that the remedy for this problem was to "wed" the pads to the existing rotors. So, I performed that as best as I could in a safe and sound manner which resulted in a continuation of the same sounds and violent pitching during braking. I continued to use them for about 4K miles until one day I approached a red stop light and stood on the brakes to make my vehicle stop and it barely responded in time to not cause an accident.  I took my car to a dealership mechanic to review and their finding was that the pads severely warped my rotors and they needed to be fully replaced, pads and rotors. Cost me an additional $200 in labor on top of what I paid for parts.  My car is now performing as it had in the past. I specifically requested and kept the parts that the dealership mechanic replaced as the Brembo pads were highly suspect to start with and I wanted to provide them as support for my claim here. If they're needed please reply back with an address to ship them to. Never once in the time I've driven my vehicle had I experienced that type of safety hazard before ~ 90K miles from November of 2012. This brake product should not be deemed safe for public roads.

issues.title: Valve Spring Failure
issues.description: Valve springs can break or fail, causing engine damage, loss of compression, and potential catastrophic engine failure. This is a well-documented issue affecting the FA20 engine.
issues.fix_description: Replace valve springs with updated parts, often requires complete engine rebuild if damage has occurred
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid high RPM until engine is warmed up, monitor for symptoms

issues.title: Fuel Pump Recall
issues.description: Low-pressure fuel pump impeller can crack and cause fuel pump to fail, resulting in engine stalling or failure to start.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump under recall - covered by manufacturer
issues.prevention: Check for recall notices and get repair completed promptly

issues.title: Airbag Inflator Recall (Takata)
issues.description: Takata airbag inflators can rupture and send metal fragments into the cabin, potentially causing serious injury or death.
issues.fix_description: Replace airbag inflator under recall - covered by manufacturer
issues.prevention: Check VIN for recall status and complete repair immediately

issues.title: Clutch Bearing Failure
issues.description: Release bearing or throw-out bearing can fail prematurely, causing clutch engagement problems and noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch release bearing and related components
issues.prevention: Avoid riding the clutch, proper clutch engagement techniques

issues.title: Carbon Build-up in Direct Injection Engine
issues.description: Direct injection engines are prone to carbon build-up on intake valves, causing reduced performance and rough idle.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, occasional highway driving, consider catch can installation

issues.title: Rear Differential Mount Failure
issues.description: Rear differential mount can crack or fail, causing vibration and clunking noises during acceleration and deceleration.
issues.fix_description: Replace rear differential mount with OEM or upgraded aftermarket part
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches and aggressive driving

issues.title: Chirping Noise from Engine Bay
issues.description: High-pitched chirping noise from engine bay, often related to direct injection system operation or accessory belts.
issues.fix_description: Replace accessory belt or address direct injection pump noise with TSB updates
issues.prevention: Regular belt inspection and replacement as needed

issues.title: Cricket Noise from Fuel Injectors
issues.description: Ticking or cricket-like noise from fuel injectors, particularly noticeable at idle. This is often normal but can indicate injector issues.
issues.fix_description: Usually normal operation, but may require injector cleaning or replacement if excessive
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel and fuel system cleaners periodically

issues.title: Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption due to piston ring design and engine tolerances, particularly in early model years.
issues.fix_description: Monitor oil level regularly, potential engine rebuild if severe
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use recommended oil viscosity

issues.title: Interior Rattles and Squeaks
issues.description: Various interior panels, dashboard, and trim pieces can develop rattles and squeaks over time.
issues.fix_description: Locate and secure loose panels, add foam padding or clips as needed

issues.title: Paint and Clear Coat Issues
issues.description: Some BRZ models experience premature paint fading, clear coat peeling, or paint chipping, particularly on horizontal surfaces.
issues.fix_description: Repaint affected areas or entire vehicle if warranty coverage applies
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, covered parking when possible

issues.title: Transmission Mount Wear
issues.description: Engine and transmission mounts can wear prematurely, causing excessive vibration and shifter movement.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn engine or transmission mounts
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive driving and hard launches

editorial.tagline: Pure rear-drive joy without the premium price
editorial.hero_blurb: The BRZ resurrects the affordable sports car formula with perfect 50/50 weight distribution and naturally aspirated thrills. This is driving in its purest form – no turbos, no all-wheel drive, just you, the road, and 200hp of perfectly balanced boxer power.
editorial.essence: The BRZ strips away modern complexity to deliver pure driving engagement through perfect weight distribution, low center of gravity, and naturally aspirated response. It's not about straight-line speed – it's about the connection between driver and machine that's been lost in today's power-obsessed market.
editorial.heritage: Born from Subaru's partnership with Toyota, the BRZ draws inspiration from classic rear-drive sports cars of the 1980s and 90s. It represents Subaru's return to their sports car roots, channeling the spirit of the original Impreza 2.5 RS while embracing modern chassis dynamics.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers prioritized feel over figures, creating a car with perfect 53/47 front-to-rear weight distribution and the lowest possible center of gravity. Every component was positioned to enhance balance, from the horizontally-opposed engine sitting low in the chassis to the rear-mounted fuel tank.
editorial.motorsport_history: While new to racing heritage, the BRZ quickly became a grassroots motorsport favorite, dominating autocross and track day events. Its balanced chassis makes it a natural choice for amateur racing series and drift competitions worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The naturally aspirated boxer four delivers linear, predictable power with a distinctive horizontal rumble. Peak torque comes early at 6,400 rpm, encouraging high-rev driving that rewards patience and precision over brute force acceleration.
editorial.transmission_feel: The six-speed manual offers precise, mechanical engagement with well-defined gates and a clutch that bites at the perfect engagement point. Each shift feels deliberate and satisfying, connecting the driver directly to the drivetrain.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The chassis is telepathic, communicating road surface changes and grip levels through every input. It encourages aggressive cornering with predictable breakaway characteristics and minimal body roll, making novices feel like heroes.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but retains genuine feedback, with consistent weighting that loads up naturally in corners. The steering responds immediately to inputs without feeling twitchy, offering confidence-inspiring precision on both road and track.
editorial.brake_confidence: Ventilated front discs provide strong, fade-resistant stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The brake balance complements the chassis perfectly, allowing trail braking and heel-toe downshifts without drama.
editorial.sound_signature: The boxer engine produces a unique horizontal growl that's distinctly Subaru, with intake sounds becoming more prominent under acceleration. The exhaust note is subtle from the factory but responds beautifully to aftermarket modifications.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who value engagement over acceleration, weekend canyon carvers, and track day enthusiasts who want affordable thrills. Perfect for those who understand that the best driving experiences happen at legal speeds.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Power seekers wanting straight-line acceleration, daily commuters needing rear seat practicality, or drivers who prioritize luxury amenities over driving dynamics.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with maintenance records and inspect for track abuse signs. The 2017+ models received a mild power bump and improved torque curve, making them slightly more desirable.

expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Subaru BRZ represents a mature, track-focused evolution with significant mechanical improvements over the previous generation. The FA24 engine brings welcome upgrades including an oil cooler and improved oil baffling, though boxer engine service remains challenging. Best suited for enthusiasts who prioritize handling dynamics over daily comfort.
